  "description": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"79v9e\",\"text\":\"This protocol describes how to make Quenching solution and Blocking solution used for protein EDAC particle coupling. Glycine serves as a primary amine source for quenching the coupling reaction. Bovine serum albumin (BSA) is used to coat particle surface to prevent nonspecific (e.g. hydrophobic) interaction. Adapted from Bangs Laboratories Inc. TechNote 205 Covalent Coupling.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
  "guidelines": "",
  "before_start": "",
  "warning": "",
  "materials_text": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"sS1PG\",\"text\":\"MATERIALS\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":null,\"entityRanges\":null,\"data\":null},{\"key\":\"8NCb6\",\"text\":\" \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":null,\"entityRanges\":[{\"key\":0,\"offset\":0,\"length\":1}],\"data\":null},{\"key\":\"J9jl5\",\"text\":\" \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":null,\"entityRanges\":[{\"key\":1,\"offset\":0,\"length\":1}],\"data\":null},{\"key\":\"83ac6\",\"text\":\"Reagents:\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"style\":\"italic\",\"offset\":0,\"length\":9},{\"style\":\"bold\",\"offset\":0,\"length\":9}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"96djs\",\"text\":\"Bovine serum albumin (BSA)\",\"type\":\"unordered-list-item\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"5ntu9\",\"text\":\"Glycine\",\"type\":\"unordered-list-item\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]}],\"entityMap\":{\"0\":{\"type\":\"reagents\",\"mutability\":\"\",\"data\":{\"id\":182099,\"guid\":\"41A983F3341F11EE9D4302C0B41BC903\",\"name\":\"Glycine\",\"mol_weight\":0,\"sku\":\"G46\",\"url\":\"https://www.fishersci.com/shop/products/glycine-crystalline-certified-fisher-chemical-2/G46500\",\"cas_number\":\"\",\"rrid\":\"\",\"vendor\":{\"id\":31,\"name\":\"Fisher Scientific\",\"link\":\"https://www.fishersci.com/us/en/home.html\",\"is_requested\":false,\"image\":{\"source\":\"/img/vendors/placeholder.png\",\"placeholder\":\"/img/vendors/placeholder.png\"}},\"is_public\":true,\"can_edit\":false}},\"1\":{\"type\":\"reagents\",\"mutability\":\"\",\"data\":{\"id\":182552,\"guid\":\"41AA22BB341F11EE9D4302C0B41BC903\",\"name\":\"BSA\",\"mol_weight\":0,\"sku\":\"#A8806\",\"url\":\"https://www.sigmaaldrich.com/catalog/product/sigma/a8806?lang=en\\u0026region=US\",\"cas_number\":\"\",\"rrid\":\"\",\"vendor\":{\"id\":17,\"name\":\"Merck MilliporeSigma (Sigma-Aldrich)\",\"link\":\"http://sigmaaldrich.com\",\"is_requested\":false,\"image\":{\"source\":\"/img/vendors/placeholder.png\",\"placeholder\":\"/img/vendors/placeholder.png\"}},\"is_public\":true,\"can_edit\":false}}}}",
  "steps": [
    "Add 100 mg BSA to 100 mL DW to make 0.1 % w/v solution. Swirl to dissolve BSA. Recommended concentration from Tech Note 205 is 0.05 % w/v - 1 % w/v BSA. Volume and concentration can be adjusted as necessary.",
    "Add 263 mg glycine to make 35 millimolar (mM) solution. Recommended concentration from Tech Note 205 is 30 millimolar (mM) - 40 millimolar (mM) glycine. Volume and concentration can be adjusted as necessary.",
    "Add 1 g BSA to 100 mL DW to make 1 % w/v solution. Swirl to dissolve BSA.",
    "Store solutions at 4 °C ."
